snippet.title: Best phones
snippet.description: Looking for phones? CNET's reviews of the best phones include photos, video, and user reviews.

snippet.title: The robo-race is on for the housecleaning crown
snippet.description: We've had several robot vacuums battle it out on our test floor. Here's what you can expect from each of them.

snippet.title: 2013 Ford C-Max Hybrid
snippet.description: Offering all the fuel economy and practical interior space of a Toyota Prius, the 2013 Ford C-Max Hybrid adds significant power and a more engaged driving experience.

snippet.title: Google retakes crown as US desktop traffic king
snippet.description: After playing second fiddle to Yahoo for the past seven months, ComScore rankings now show the Web giant back on top.

snippet.title: HTC One takes display pixel density crown
snippet.description: The HTC One ups the ante on the iPhone 5, packing more pixels closer together than Apple's touted Retina technology.

snippet.title: AwoX StriimLight B-10
snippet.description: The StriimLight B-10 and StriimLight Wi-Fi are LEDs with integrated speakers that let you adjust music volume and bulb brightness from your couch.

snippet.title: DeGeneres' Oscar selfie tweet captures retweet crown
snippet.description: A star-studded tweet by the Oscars host quickly blows past President Obama's re-election tweet from 2012.

snippet.title: V-Moda XS on-ear headphones
snippet.description: If you're looking for a $150-$250 on-ear headphone, the well-built V-Moda XS should be on your short list.

snippet.title: IBM defends US patent crown in 2013
snippet.description: Google and Apple also crack the top 20 in patents -- but the search giant has a slight edge in patents awarded.

snippet.title: The Walk Fitness Tracker Game
snippet.description: Despite its complex interface and high download price, The Walk: Fitness Tracker Game is an excellent way to make your daily walk interesting again.
